data.entities: yellow cake mix | eggs | cream cheese | butter | confectioners sugar | lemon juice
data.sentence: 1 box yellow cake mix, 2 eggs, 1 (8 oz.) pkg. cream cheese, softened, 1 stick butter or margarine, 1 (1 lb.) box confectioners sugar, 1/4 lemon juice Mix cake mix 1 egg and butter together. Press into bottom and side of pan (9 x 12-inch). Then mix cream cheese 1 egg confectioners sugar and lemon juice. Pour over mixture. Bake at 325\u00b0 for 50 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

data.entities: crescent rolls | cream cheese | mayo | crescent rolls
data.sentence: pat crescent rolls in jelly roll pan. bake for 6 to 8 minutes. mix together cream cheese, dressing and mayo. top cooled crescent rolls. add remaining ingredients. refrigerate.

data.entities: mix | baking | mix | sugar | orange | margarine
data.sentence: heat oven to 400°. mix baking mix, 1/4 cup sugar and the orange peel. cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. press mixture in bottom of ungreased round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch. bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes. cool about 30 minutes.

data.entities: oil | pepper | garlic | salt | pepper | vinegar | bread | garlic | olive | oil | mozzarella cheese | basil
data.sentence: heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. add the pepper strips and saute until lightly browned at the edges and beginning to soften, about 5 minutes. reduce the heat to medium low, stir in the minced garlic, cover and continue cooking until soft, about 8 minutes longer, stirring occasionally. season with salt and pepper to taste; remove from heat and stir in the vinegar. grill the bread over a medium heat, turning once, until golden brown on both sides, 1 to 2 minutes. place the toast slices on a large platter, rub the peeled garlic over the tops, and brush with the remaining olive oil. place a few slices of mozzarella cheese on each toast. cover with a portion of the sauteed peppers, the top with a sprinkling of basil. serve immediately.

data.entities: green onions | butter | flour | cayenne pepper | milk | dressing | catsup | crab | crab | asparagus
data.sentence: cook green onions in butter until tender. stir in flour and cayenne pepper. add milk. stir until thickened. remove from heat. stir in ranch dressing, catsup and crab. heat, but do not cook. spoon warm crab over cooked asparagus. sprinkle with parmesan. broil 3 to 4 minutes (until lightly browned). serve over toast. (an attractive and easy dish for company.)

data.entities: flour tortillas | Serrano ham | grated cheese | scallion | vegetable oil
data.sentence: 1 (6 inch) soft flour tortillas, 2 slices serrano ham or 2 slices prosciutto, preferred, 14-12 cup grated cheese, any type you like, 12 scallion, sliced fine, 3 -4 slices pickled jalapeno peppers, minced (from a jar), 1 teaspoon vegetable oil Preheat a stovetop griddle or skillet. Place ham over the entire surface of the tortilla. Cover 1/2 the surface with cheese scallion and jalapeno. Fold tortilla over. Brush both sides with oil. Place on griddle (or skillet) and cook until grill marks appear (or it turns brown) 1-2 minutes per side. Cut into 3-4 wedges and serve.

data.entities: macaroni shells | green onions | bacon bits | Mayonnaise | lemon juice | parmesan cheese | sugar | garlic powder | bite size salad greens | zucchini | cauliflowerets | broccoli flowerets | tomatoes
data.sentence: 1 (7 to 8 oz.) pkg. macaroni shells, 1/2 c. sliced green onions, 1/2 c. bacon bits, 1 c. mayonnaise, 1/4 c. lemon juice, 3 tsp. grated Parmesan cheese, 1 tsp. sugar, 1/2 tsp. garlic powder, 4 c. bite size salad greens, 1 medium zucchini, sliced, 1 c. sliced cauliflowerets, 1 c. broccoli flowerets, 2 medium tomatoes, cut into wedges Cook macaroni as per package directions and drain. Rinse with cold water; drain again. Stir together macaroni onions and bacon bits in medium bowl. Mix mayonnaise lemon juice cheese sugar and garlic powder. In 3 1/2-quart salad bowl layer salad greens macaroni mixture zucchini and cauliflowerets. On top of this layer broccoli and tomatoes. Pour dressing evenly over top. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Sprinkle with bacon bits just before serving. Refrigerate only remaining salad. Makes 10 servings.

1 34 ounces premium gin, 14 ounce green chartreuse liqueur, 2 fresh sage leaves, ice In a cocktail shaker filled with ice add gin and chartreuse. Stir until well chilled. Run a fresh sage leaf around the rim of a martini glass. Strain alcohol into martini glass and garnish with a fresh sage leaf. Enjoy!

data.entities: nuts | Cheerios | rice squares | pretzel bites | salad oil | Worcestershire sauce | garlic salt | seasoning salt
data.sentence: 2 lb. mixed salted nuts, 10 1/2 oz. pkg. Cheerios, 6 1/2 oz. pkg. rice squares, 6 1/2 oz. pkg. pretzel bites, 5 1/2 oz. stem pretzel sticks, 2 c. salad oil, 2 Tbsp. Worcestershire sauce, 1 tsp. garlic salt, 1 tsp. seasoning salt Mix oil and sauce together. Mix all ingredients. Bake at 250\u00b0 for 2 hours stirring every 15 minutes. Store in cans tins jars or plastic bags.

data.entities: vanilla | egg whites | sugar | cornstarch | vanilla | butter | milk | vanilla | powdered sugar | peanut butter | vanilla | egg whites | sugar | peanut butter
data.sentence: make vanilla filling: set aside the egg whites. cook 1 cup sugar, cornstarch, vanilla, butter and milk until thick, pour half of the vanilla filling in a deep dish pie shell and set aside. then take powdered sugar and peanut butter, mix until crumbly, pour 3/4 cup of crumbs on filling. pour remaining vanilla filling on top of crust. beat egg whites until peaks form. add 2 tablespoons sugar, beat until stiff. spread on pie. put remaining peanut butter crumbs on top of pie. cook at 325° until brown.
